<SLUG> BC-NORDSTROM-BEANIE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BEANIE BUYERS BLITZ NORDSTROM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY ENRIQUE RIVERO  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Beanie Babies have gone upscale.
</P>
<P>
   Hundreds of people lined up at a Nordstrom department store
hours before it opened Wednesday so they could buy a few
hard-to-get members of the doll set causing a national hysteria.
</P>
<P>
   Cathy Keating, manager at the upscale retailer's girls
department, said customers were already crowded around the entrance
when she arrived for work nearly two hours before the store's 10
a.m. opening.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was, like, Wow. I couldn't believe there were that many cars
in the parking lot,'' Keating said. ``I heard from (employees in)
our housekeeping (department) that people were here in sleeping
bags at 2:30 this morning.''
</P>
<P>
   Beanie Babies have become a cultural phenomenon. McDonald's sold
an estimated 150million Teenie Beanie Babies in two weeks this
month after a similar run last spring. Internet sites dedicated to
Beanie Babies report some of the dolls are selling for as much as
$10,000.
</P>
<P>
   Keating wouldn't say how many dolls were in Wednesday's shipment
but said they were all sold by 11 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   About a third of the Topanga Plaza store's shipment included the
extremely hard-to-get Peace the Bear, Valentino, Curly and Erin
dolls.
</P>
<P>
   Erin is selling for up to $300 on the street and some other
styles are also fetching top dollar, said Keating, adding that one
shopper said she paid $100 for one of the dolls Nordstrom was
selling for $4.95. HOW'D THEY KNOW? So how did hundreds of
customers who arrived up to eight hours before opening know the
Beanie Babies would be at the Topanga Plaza Nordstrom? Nordstrom
told them.
</P>
<P>
   The Seattle-based retail chain has a Beanie Babies hotline
``because we get so many calls about them,'' said Leslie Harris,
the company's statewide public relations director.
</P>
<P>
   When store managers in Southern California learn about a Beanie
Babies shipment, they update the hotline.
</P>
<P>
   The phone number for the L.A. area is (310) 750-2627. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
