stake and after little debate, New Jersey lawmakers are poised to
adopt legislation governing the reorganization of Prudential
Insurance Co. of America that consumer advocates say contains
troubling loopholes that could shortchange nearly 11 million
policyholders. By Joseph B. Treaster.
</P>
<P>
   CONFERENCE-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ The American Advertising
Federation, at its annual conference, is undertaking what is
intended to be a major multiyear communications initiative to
promote and demonstrate the importance of advertising to marketers
and consumers. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ECONSCENE (Undated) _ With Japan slipping into recession
and the yen sagging to an eight-year low, the Clinton
administration has finally intervened to prop up the beleaguered
Japanese currency. No one is claiming that the intervention is more
than a palliative. One way or another Japan must jump-start its
long-sputtering economy. By Peter Passell.
</P>
