   CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN-TEX (Undated) _ In just two years on the
market, the Chrysler Sebring convertible has become the
best-selling open-top car in the nation, commanding one-third of
all ragtop vehicle sales last year. There's good reason for that.
This is the only affordable convertible that provides roomy,
comfortable seating for up to four adults. By G. Chambers Williams
III.
</P>
