   JAPAN-ASSESS (Tokyo) _ In a few weeks, Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto will face nationwide elections as he presides over the
worst recession in more than half a century, a limp stock market
and the highest unemployment rate since records began to be kept.
Yet his governing Liberal Democratic Party is expected to do very
well. Analysis by Nicholas Kristof.
</P>
