   &UR; NATIONAL &LR;  (Coded a)
</P>
<P>
   IND-TRAIN-CRASH (Portage, Ind.) _ A Chicago-bound commuter train
struck a tractor-trailer at a railroad crossing early Thursday,
killing three people and injuring two when a steel coil from the
truck crashed into the train.
</P>
<P>
   PUERTO-PHONE-STRIKE (San Juan, P.R.) _ More than 6,000 telephone
company employees went on strike Thursday, vowing to cripple
telephone service in the island of 3.7 million residents in order
to stop the sale of ``a national patrimony.'' Privatization that
has proven popular in other countries as a way to improve
telecommunications services and raise cash has been met here by
protests, sabotage and even a war declaration by a clandestine
political group. By Mireya Navarro.
