the globe, from Russia to Latin America. The problem, Clinton aides
readily admit, is that the huge currency intervention the United
States launched Wednesday actually takes some of the pressure off
Japan to act _ and unless Japan acts, the temporary effects of
buying yen will be washed away. By David E. Sanger.
