Business, the nation's premier small-business lobby, opened its
first-ever legislative summit Thursday. In panel discussions and
brainstorming sessions, participants bashed the Endangered Species
Act , the tax code and public elementary schools for allowing
environmental groups to set curricula and portray business as an
enemy. ``The children come out as little greens,'' one participant
said. Story will include activities of Waco and Austin delegates.
(Moscoso, Cox News Service)..
</P>
