<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-18 14:54 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5361 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ENTERTAINMENT-BUDGET-     06-18 0437
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ENTERTAINMENT-BUDGET-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
.
</HEADLINE>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
. 
MULAN-MOVIE (Los Angeles) _ Disney's new animated musical breaks
the mold a bit with its new animated film, featuring a heroic young
woman who doesn't need any help from a man and has both of her
parents still alive. This excellent film demonstrates, yet again,
that Disney still has the magic touch when it comes to animation.
By Glenn Whipp. 
. 
WESTERN-FILMS (Los Angeles) _ Seeing a western on anything other
than a wide screen is like a one-horse town with a hanging judge.
It doesn't do justice. Like-minded movie-watchers will be glad to
hear that Laemmle salutes 75 years of Warner Bros. westerns with a
summer full of them. By Bob McCarthy. 
. 
MULAN-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ ``Mulan'' stands on its own as an
example of what the Mouse House still does best _ classic
storytelling, bold animation technique and zippy songs. These
elements combine to make this Disney's most appealing animated film
since ``The Lion King.'' 3{ Stars. By Glenn Whipp. 
. 
XFILES-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ First off, a disclaimer: I don't
believe in UFOs, aliens or Trilateralists. Roswell is just a spot
on the map, LBJ didn't whack JFK, and O.J. was not set up by the
Japanese mafia.I do believe in good movies, though, so I was
curious. Could I watch the ``X-Files'' film and not become lost in
a murky labyrinth understood only to Internet geeks and dateless
shut-ins? 3 Stars. By Glenn Whipp. 
. 
X-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ We learn more and understand less from
``The X-Files'' movie. Really, did you expect it to be any other
way? Fans of the TV show, and I'm one of them, have gotten used to
the somewhat radical concept of inconclusiveness as part of the
fun. Even when things are resolved in the series _ a monster
caught, an innocent exorcised _ it's always with an edgy, ``but
...'' attached. 3 Stars. By Bob Strauss. 
. 
DREAM-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ A sweet little film that convincingly
shows the blush and rush of first love. 3 Stars. By Glenn Whipp. 
. 
NILE-MUSIC (Los Angeles) _ We catch up with Nile Rodgers, who with
late partner Bernard Edwards put the funk in disco supergroup Chic.
By Fred Shuster. 
. 
POP-BEAT (Los Angeles) _ Caramel singer-bassist Andy Curran
collects vintage effects pedals that made it into his self-titled
debut for Geffen Records. By Fred Shuster. 
. 

