   OHIO -- FARM-GOP. Republicans, led by Sen. Conrad Burns,
R-Montana, held a press conference today defending the 1996
``Freedom to Farm'' act, but blaming low farm prices on poor trade
policy. After meeting with 11 farm organizations, GOP senators said
they would push for passage of fast-track track authority and
changes in economic sanctions to improve the export economy for
farmers. Hurt
</P>
