<SLUG> BC-MULAN-DONNY-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Osmond goes a bit Disney in `Mulan'
 &HT;    BySteve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA -- The first thing Donny Osmond wants to know is if
Rupert's is still open. ``I remember doing a show there in '89,''
he says by phone. ``That was a cool place.''
</P>
<P>
   Well, no more. The Atlanta dance club is now Atlanta Live.
</P>
<P>
   Now on to the main topic: His one-song performance in ``Mulan,''
the new animated Disney feature.
</P>
<P>
   He got the job after losing out on last year's ``Hercules.'' He
auditioned for it, ``but they told me my voice was a little too
deep. I was really depressed, because I wanted to do it so badly.''
</P>
<P>
   Luckily, they kept his tape, and found that it matched nicely
with the hero of ``Mulan,'' an army captain whose speaking voice is
performed by Broadway and film actor B.D. Wong.
</P>
<P>
   Osmond showed up at the studio to record, but first spent an
hour with the movie's producers ... who gave him too much
information. ``All they had at the time were pencil sketches of the
character. So they explained his background, his personality. They
said, `He's a little bit vulnerable but also strong, and he's
training an army. Now go sing.'''
</P>
<P>
   Though some boys may think ``Mulan'' looks like a chick flick,
Osmond got the thumbs up from his 13-year-old son (one of his five
boys, ranging in age from newborn to 19). ``I watched him while he
was watching the movie. It was a great barometer to see how that
age range reacts. I asked him what he liked about it, and he said
he thought the story was fabulous.''
</P>
<P>
   As you'd expect with a family of five kids, Osmond's house is
full of Disney videotapes. His personal favorite?
</P>
<P>
   ``I love `Toy Story.' I think it's my favorite Disney classic.
And I know it sounds biased, but `Mulan' runs a very close
second.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
