<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILES-GUIDE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Catching up: An X-tremely weird world
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA -- For five years, fans of the ``The X-Files'' have been
slowly immersed in a byzantine world of aliens (good and bad),
genetic engineering, shadowy government operatives and massive
cover-ups. Creator Chris Carter has concocted one of the most
diabolically complicated worlds ever created for the mass media.
</P>
<P>
   If you're coming to the movie ``The X-Files: Fight the Future''
as a neophyte, or have followed the show without obsessing on how
it all fits together, here's a quick cheat sheet to get you up to
speed on what's known and what's conjectured.
</P>
<P>
   Who's who
</P>
<P>
   FBI Special Agent Fox Mulder (David Duchovny) _ Brilliant but
darkly obsessed agent who believes his sister, Samantha, was
abducted by aliens as a child. On his quest, he is uncovering
pieces of a far-reaching conspiracy involving an alien attempt to
colonize Earth and powerful men who are helping the aliens.
</P>
<P>
   FBI Special Agent Dana Scully (Gillian Anderson) _ Mulder's
partner, who usually plays a scientific and rational role to his
intuitive, seat-of-the-pants style.
</P>
<P>
   FBI Assistant Director Walter Skinner (Mitch Pileggi) _ Mulder
and Scully's boss, he's mainly a benevolent protector who looks out
for them, but sometimes tries to rein them in.
</P>
<P>
   Cigarette-Smoking Man (William B. Davis) _ Shadowy unnamed
figure who's somehow a key. Works for the Syndicate (see below) but
may have his own agenda.
</P>
<P>
   Well-Manicured Man (John Neville) _ Minor character in the
series becomes crucial in the movie. Unnamed British Syndicate
figure.
</P>
<P>
   The Syndicate _ Top-secret international cabal that has
conspired with aliens to take over and colonize Earth.
</P>
<P>
   What's what
</P>
<P>
   The X-Files _ Secret FBI files on cases involving unexplained
phenomena (X  &QC;  unexplained). On the series, these can involve all
sorts of spooky stuff, including vampires, werewolves, telekinesis,
etc. The important ones are about aliens and are part of the core
mythology of the series.
</P>
<P>
   The aliens _ There are believed to be at least two kinds, maybe
more. The bad aliens are attempting to colonize and enslave Earth
and use their life force, a black, oily substance, to take over
humans. They have been here for thousands of years, although it's
not clear yet what is taking so long. Some good aliens, who are
shape-shifters and can take human form, may be fighting the bad
aliens, but they are involved in the TV series, not the movie.
</P>
<P>
   On the web
</P>
<P>
   There are hundreds of ``X-Files'' Web sites. A few key ones:
</P>
<P>
   http://www.astolat.demon.co.uk _ A good overview of what's been
figured out and deduced so far on the conspiracy theories.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.AnotherUniverse.com/columns/amhh/amvvhh0605982.html _
On the movie soundtrack, Chris Carter recorded a ``hidden track''
at the end, in which he talks about the background of the Syndicate
and the alien takeover. An unofficial transcript (with
misspellings) is available here, on Another Universe's page.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.geocities.com/Area51/Cavern/7094/Cafe/cafe.html _
Some of the most thorough and thoughtful episode summaries are done
by Barbara Ruef on her site called Cafe Barbara.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.usd.edu/(tilde)mmarek/xf/movie.html _ If you want
some of the movie's secrets divulged (``spoilers'' in Net jargon),
go here.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.thex-files.com _ The TV series' official Web site.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.fightthefuture.com _ The movie's official Web site.
It doesn't offer nearly as much information as the unofficial
sites, but you can download the movie trailer if you have a fast
modem and plenty of time.
</P>
<P>
   On video
</P>
<P>
   Fox Broadcasting Co. has released 30 ``X-Files'' episodes from
the first three seasons on home video, available for rental or sale
at most major outlets. You can't really get a thorough grounding in
the intricacies of the show's mythology, because several key
episodes from this past season aren't out yet. If you want to get a
taste for the show, just get the pilot episode, which introduces
the major players.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
