<P>
   IRAN-SOCCER _ TEHRAN, Iran _ The U.S. plays Iran in the World
Cup soccer tournament Sunday. Except when Iraq is in crisis, Iran
is probably the biggest story in the Middle East right now. There
were huge street celebrations when Iran made the tournament. People
said they bordered on political outbursts. Iranian President
Khatami recently threatened an ``explosion'' if the conservative
Islamists don't relax their grip on the public. (Kaplow, Cox News
Service).
</P>
