<P>
   BETHUNE _ HOUSTON -- Gordon Bethune is riding high as the CEO of
resurgent Continental Airlines and the author of a new book ``Worst
to First,'' that chronicles its resurrection from years of failure.
A shoot-from-the hip type who dropped out of high school and rides
motorcycles to relax, Bethune has plenty of opinions about how to
run an airline, as well as about Atlanta rival Delta, which he
would now be running if he'd had his way. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 35.
