<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Mass., N.J., W.Va., N.J., N.Y.)   (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Watts Industries Inc., North Andover, Mass., a maker of valves
used in plumbing and heating, agreed to buy Hoke Inc., Cresskill,
N.J., a company that also makes valves. The terms were not
disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Horizon Bancorp Inc., Beckley, W.Va., and Bank of Mingo, Mingo
County, W.Va., have called off Horizon's purchase of Mingo because
the two banks were unable to agree onto final terms and conditions.
</P>
<P>
   Becton, Dickinson &AMP; Co., Franklin Lakes, N.J., said it would
close a plant in Hancock, N.Y., by May 2000. The plant, which makes
surgical products, is being closed as part of a program to cut
costs.
</P>
